  <entry>
    <title>Curriculum Vitae</title>
    <url>/CV/index.html</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<link rel="stylesheet" class="aplayer-secondary-style-marker" href="\assets\css\APlayer.min.css"><script src="\assets\js\APlayer.min.js" class="aplayer-secondary-script-marker"></script><script class="meting-secondary-script-marker" src="\assets\js\Meting.min.js"></script><p><font size="5"><strong>Pengcheng Li</strong> (<strong>Lǐ Péngchéng</strong>/李鹏程)</font></p>
<div class="note "><h4>Personal Info</h4></div>  
<ul>
<li>Basic: Born at Gao’an city, Jiangxi province, People’s Republic of China.</li>
<li>Title: Dr. Pengcheng Li, graduated from AMSS, UCAS in 2020.</li>
<li>Email: <span class="exturl" data-url="bWFpbHRvOnhpYW90aWFuc2hpc2hvdUAxNjMuY29t">xiaotianshishou@163.com<i class="fa fa-external-link-alt"></i></span> or <span class="exturl" data-url="bWFpbHRvOmxpcGNhdHlAYW1zcy5hYy5jbg==">lipcaty@amss.ac.cn<i class="fa fa-external-link-alt"></i></span></li>
<li>Address: AMSS, UCAS, No.55 Zhongguancun Road, Haidian District, Beijing, China (100190).</li>
</ul>
<div class="note "><h4>Background</h4></div>  
<ul>
<li>
<p>2020: Ph.D. in Pure Mathematics, AMSS, UCAS; advisor: Researcher Jianzhong Pan.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>2015: B.S. in Mathematics and Applied Mathematics, School of Mathematics, Dalian University of Technology.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<div class="note "><h4>Research Interests</h4></div>  
<ul>
<li>
<p>Homotopy theory. I am particularly interested in the homotopy theory of Moore spaces and Chang complexes. I am also interested in the homotopy theory of Poincaré Duality complexes and manifolds.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Mathematical education.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<div style="text-align:center;"><a class="btn" href="https://www.researchgate.net/account.UserCV.getCV.html?cvId=5ed4a79844aad26e7834dd06" target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="CV">
<i class="far fa-file-pdf fa-fw fa-lg"></i>PDF Copy
</a></div>
